dct_title_s: Eastern Turkey in Asia. Meskene, sheet 29. Series I.D.W.O. no. 1522
dct_description_sm: " Lithd. at the Intell: Div: War Office June 1902." Relief shown by form lines and by spot heights. Includes an index to adjoining sheets, and a glossary. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. no. 1522. Great Britain. War Office. Intelligence Division. I.D.W.O. no. 1522. Relief shown by form lines and spot heights. Some sheets from this set were revised and issued by War Office. Geographical Section. General Staff, published as G.S.G.S. no. 1522, 1522a. Series covers Mesopotamia and eastern Anatolian parts of Ottoman Empire. "Compied at the Intelligence division, War Office by Major F.R. Maunsell, R.A. from Chesney's Euphrates Expedition 1839, Col M.S. Bell 1886, Oppenheim's 'Vom Mittlemeer zum Persischen Golf' 1893, Kartevon Kleinasien - R. Kiepert - sheet Haleb 1911, Saare & Hersfeld Archaeologische Reise in Euphrate & Tigris Gebiet 1908, Capt. M. Sykes 1906, Dr. Hinriches 1911. Corrected to Nov. 1915." With glossary. Set is complete, see index.
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain. War Office. Intelligence Division
